{
  "_comment": "RES-2 — baseline seccomp profile for the docgrok-pipeline-worker. Allow-list of syscalls needed by Python + PyMuPDF + Pillow + httpx + multiprocessing.spawn. All other syscalls return EPERM. Apply via Pod securityContext.seccompProfile.localhostProfile=docgrok-parser.json (file must be at /var/lib/kubelet/seccomp/ on each node). Tightened in batch 8: removed chmod/chown family, mknod, inotify*, sysv-IPC msgget/msgrcv/msgsnd, ptrace, set/getuid* — the parser does not change perms or ownership, does not watch filesystems, and does not use SysV IPC. If a workload error references one of these, run docgrok-parser-audit.json (SCMP_ACT_LOG) for one ingestion cycle and selectively re-add the syscall.",
  "_origin": "Generated from strace of pipeline-worker on Ubuntu 22.04 + spot-checked against Docker's default profile (https://docs.docker.com/engine/security/seccomp/). Tightened batch 8.",
